          <td style=3D"padding-bottom: 36px; color: #000000; font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">For many, this year=
=E2=80=99s first-half auction total of around $2.87 billion seemed like a t=
otal drag. But despite the dreary narrative, 1H24 saw a pronounced rise in =
both the percentage sold above low estimate and the sell-through rate. Does=
 this presage a stronger season in the fall? <br/><br/>Maybe. Volume will d=
epend more upon the consignments than any other factor, but these numbers a=
re encouraging. Remember, when the auction houses pitch clients on whether =
to consign, they=E2=80=99re using some of this same data to make their case=
=2E It=E2=80=99s not foolproof: There was=20=
a rise in 1H22 that was followed by=
 falling auction totals. And, of course, this is a small sample size. Never=
theless, we=E2=80=99re beginning to see encouraging patterns. <br/></td>
